mixin tabs(n)
  //-
    NOTE this mixin *must* be called with an id attribute as shown below.
    The id is required and is used to calculate the `name` attributes of the radio button inputs.
    Without an id, the radio buttons may not work correctly.
    The id is added to the mixin as any attribute would be added to an element:
    ```
    +tabs(3)(id="any-valid-id-string")
      mixin tab(i)
        ...
      mixin panel(i)
        ...
    ```
    Or, you may use the shorthand id syntax:
    ```
    +tabs(3)#any-valid-id
    ```
  dl.o-Grid.o-Tabs&attributes(attributes)
    mixin tab(i)
      | tab #{i}
    mixin panel(i)
      | panel #{i}
    block
    each val,index in new Array(n)
      dt.o-Grid__Item.o-Tabs__Tab: label.h-Block
        input.o-Tabs__Check.h-Hidden.-ps-a(type="radio" name=attributes.id value=index)&attributes((index===0) ? {checked:''} : {})
        +tab(index)
      dd.o-Grid__Item.o-Tabs__Panel
        +panel(index)
